main event: On October 21, 1964, a civilian witnessed three lights in the sky over Fosterdale, New York.
interesting points: The lights were observed for approximately 20 minutes and showed no audible sound., The witness estimated the object to be about 50 feet in diameter., Project Blue Book was notified for further investigation., Possible explanations for the lights include stars or satellites., The report did not contain any photograph evidence.
witness description: a resident of Fosterdale, New York
